143/// Helper class with most of the code for saving a value for a
144/// conditional expression cleanup.
145struct DominatingLLVMValue {
146 typedef llvm::PointerIntPair<llvm::Value*, 1, bool> saved_type;
147
148 /// Answer whether the given value needs extra work to be saved.
149 static bool needsSaving(llvm::Value *value) {
150 // If it's not an instruction, we don't need to save.
151 if (!isa<llvm::Instruction>(value)) return false;
152
153 // If it's an instruction in the entry block, we don't need to save.
154 llvm::BasicBlock *block = cast<llvm::Instruction>(value)->getParent();
155 return (block != &block->getParent()->getEntryBlock());
156 }
157
158 static saved_type save(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *value);
159 static llvm::Value *restore(CodeGenFunction &CGF, saved_type value);
160};
161
162/// A partial specialization of DominatingValue for llvm::Values that
163/// might be llvm::Instructions.
164template <class T> struct DominatingPointer<T,true> : DominatingLLVMValue {
165 typedef T *type;
166 static type restore(CodeGenFunction &CGF, saved_type value) {
167 return static_cast<T*>(DominatingLLVMValue::restore(CGF, value));
168 }
169};
170
171/// A specialization of DominatingValue for Address.
172template <> struct DominatingValue<Address> {
173 typedef Address type;
174
175 struct saved_type {
176 DominatingLLVMValue::saved_type SavedValue;
177 CharUnits Alignment;
178 };
179
180 static bool needsSaving(type value) {
181 return DominatingLLVMValue::needsSaving(value.getPointer());
182 }
183 static saved_type save(CodeGenFunction &CGF, type value) {
184 return { DominatingLLVMValue::save(CGF, value.getPointer()),
185 value.getAlignment() };
186 }
187 static type restore(CodeGenFunction &CGF, saved_type value) {
188 return Address(DominatingLLVMValue::restore(CGF, value.SavedValue),
189 value.Alignment);
190 }
191};
192
193/// A specialization of DominatingValue for RValue.
194template <> struct DominatingValue<RValue> {
195 typedef RValue type;
196 class saved_type {
197 enum Kind { ScalarLiteral, ScalarAddress, AggregateLiteral,
198 AggregateAddress, ComplexAddress };
199
200 llvm::Value *Value;
201 unsigned K : 3;
202 unsigned Align : 29;
203 saved_type(llvm::Value *v, Kind k, unsigned a = 0)
204 : Value(v), K(k), Align(a) {}
205
206 public:
207 static bool needsSaving(RValue value);
208 static saved_type save(CodeGenFunction &CGF, RValue value);
209 RValue restore(CodeGenFunction &CGF);
210
211 // implementations in CGCleanup.cpp
212 };
213
214 static bool needsSaving(type value) {
215 return saved_type::needsSaving(value);
216 }
217 static saved_type save(CodeGenFunction &CGF, type value) {
218 return saved_type::save(CGF, value);
219 }
220 static type restore(CodeGenFunction &CGF, saved_type value) {
221 return value.restore(CGF);
222 }
223};

235 /// A jump destination is an abstract label, branching to which may
236 /// require a jump out through normal cleanups.
237 struct JumpDest {
238 JumpDest() : Block(nullptr), ScopeDepth(), Index(0) {}
239 JumpDest(llvm::BasicBlock *Block,
240 EHScopeStack::stable_iterator Depth,
241 unsigned Index)
242 : Block(Block), ScopeDepth(Depth), Index(Index) {}
243
244 bool isValid() const { return Block != nullptr; }
245 llvm::BasicBlock *getBlock() const { return Block; }
246 EHScopeStack::stable_iterator getScopeDepth() const { return ScopeDepth; }
247 unsigned getDestIndex() const { return Index; }
248
249 // This should be used cautiously.
250 void setScopeDepth(EHScopeStack::stable_iterator depth) {
251 ScopeDepth = depth;
252 }
253
254 private:
255 llvm::BasicBlock *Block;
256 EHScopeStack::stable_iterator ScopeDepth;
257 unsigned Index;
258 };

344 /// API for captured statement code generation.
345 class CGCapturedStmtInfo {
346 public:
347 explicit CGCapturedStmtInfo(CapturedRegionKind K = CR_Default)
348 : Kind(K), ThisValue(nullptr), CXXThisFieldDecl(nullptr) {}
349 explicit CGCapturedStmtInfo(const CapturedStmt &S,
350 CapturedRegionKind K = CR_Default)
351 : Kind(K), ThisValue(nullptr), CXXThisFieldDecl(nullptr) {
352
353 RecordDecl::field_iterator Field =
354 S.getCapturedRecordDecl()->field_begin();
355 for (CapturedStmt::const_capture_iterator I = S.capture_begin(),
356 E = S.capture_end();
357 I != E; ++I, ++Field) {
358 if (I->capturesThis())
359 CXXThisFieldDecl = *Field;
360 else if (I->capturesVariable())
361 CaptureFields[I->getCapturedVar()->getCanonicalDecl()] = *Field;
362 else if (I->capturesVariableByCopy())
363 CaptureFields[I->getCapturedVar()->getCanonicalDecl()] = *Field;
364 }
365 }
366
367 virtual ~CGCapturedStmtInfo();
368
369 CapturedRegionKind getKind() const { return Kind; }
370
371 virtual void setContextValue(llvm::Value *V) { ThisValue = V; }
372 // Retrieve the value of the context parameter.
373 virtual llvm::Value *getContextValue() const { return ThisValue; }
374
375 /// Lookup the captured field decl for a variable.
376 virtual const FieldDecl *lookup(const VarDecl *VD) const {
377 return CaptureFields.lookup(VD->getCanonicalDecl());
378 }
379
380 bool isCXXThisExprCaptured() const { return getThisFieldDecl() != nullptr; }
381 virtual FieldDecl *getThisFieldDecl() const { return CXXThisFieldDecl; }
382
383 static bool classof(const CGCapturedStmtInfo *) {
384 return true;
385 }
386
387 /// Emit the captured statement body.
388 virtual void EmitBody(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Stmt *S) {
389 CGF.incrementProfileCounter(S);
390 CGF.EmitStmt(S);
391 }
392
393 /// Get the name of the capture helper.
394 virtual StringRef getHelperName() const { return "__captured_stmt"; }
395
396 private:
397 /// The kind of captured statement being generated.
398 CapturedRegionKind Kind;
399
400 /// Keep the map between VarDecl and FieldDecl.
401 llvm::SmallDenseMap<const VarDecl *, FieldDecl *> CaptureFields;
402
403 /// The base address of the captured record, passed in as the first
404 /// argument of the parallel region function.
405 llvm::Value *ThisValue;
406
407 /// Captured 'this' type.
408 FieldDecl *CXXThisFieldDecl;
409 };

598 /// pushFullExprCleanup - Push a cleanup to be run at the end of the
599 /// current full-expression. Safe against the possibility that
600 /// we're currently inside a conditionally-evaluated expression.
601 template <class T, class... As>
602 void pushFullExprCleanup(CleanupKind kind, As... A) {
603 // If we're not in a conditional branch, or if none of the
604 // arguments requires saving, then use the unconditional cleanup.
605 if (!isInConditionalBranch())
606 return EHStack.pushCleanup<T>(kind, A...);
607
608 // Stash values in a tuple so we can guarantee the order of saves.
609 typedef std::tuple<typename DominatingValue<As>::saved_type...> SavedTuple;
610 SavedTuple Saved{saveValueInCond(A)...};
611
612 typedef EHScopeStack::ConditionalCleanup<T, As...> CleanupType;
613 EHStack.pushCleanupTuple<CleanupType>(kind, Saved);
614 initFullExprCleanup();
615 }
616
617 /// Queue a cleanup to be pushed after finishing the current
618 /// full-expression.
619 template <class T, class... As>
620 void pushCleanupAfterFullExpr(CleanupKind Kind, As... A) {
621 if (!isInConditionalBranch())
622 return pushCleanupAfterFullExprImpl<T>(Kind, Address::invalid(), A...);
623
624 Address ActiveFlag = createCleanupActiveFlag();
625 assert(!DominatingValue<Address>::needsSaving(ActiveFlag) &&
626 "cleanup active flag should never need saving");
627
628 typedef std::tuple<typename DominatingValue<As>::saved_type...> SavedTuple;
629 SavedTuple Saved{saveValueInCond(A)...};
630
631 typedef EHScopeStack::ConditionalCleanup<T, As...> CleanupType;
632 pushCleanupAfterFullExprImpl<CleanupType>(Kind, ActiveFlag, Saved);
633 }
634
635 template <class T, class... As>
636 void pushCleanupAfterFullExprImpl(CleanupKind Kind, Address ActiveFlag,
637 As... A) {
638 LifetimeExtendedCleanupHeader Header = {sizeof(T), Kind,
639 ActiveFlag.isValid()};
640
641 size_t OldSize = LifetimeExtendedCleanupStack.size();
642 LifetimeExtendedCleanupStack.resize(
643 LifetimeExtendedCleanupStack.size() + sizeof(Header) + Header.Size +
644 (Header.IsConditional ? sizeof(ActiveFlag) : 0));
645
646 static_assert(sizeof(Header) % alignof(T) == 0,
647 "Cleanup will be allocated on misaligned address");
648 char *Buffer = &LifetimeExtendedCleanupStack[OldSize];
649 new (Buffer) LifetimeExtendedCleanupHeader(Header);
650 new (Buffer + sizeof(Header)) T(A...);
651 if (Header.IsConditional)
652 new (Buffer + sizeof(Header) + sizeof(T)) Address(ActiveFlag);
653 }

655 /// Set up the last cleanup that was pushed as a conditional
656 /// full-expression cleanup.

658 initFullExprCleanupWithFlag(createCleanupActiveFlag());

700 /// Enters a new scope for capturing cleanups, all of which
701 /// will be executed once the scope is exited.
702 class RunCleanupsScope {
703 EHScopeStack::stable_iterator CleanupStackDepth, OldCleanupScopeDepth;
704 size_t LifetimeExtendedCleanupStackSize;
705 bool OldDidCallStackSave;
706 protected:
707 bool PerformCleanup;
708 private:
709
710 RunCleanupsScope(const RunCleanupsScope &) = delete;
711 void operator=(const RunCleanupsScope &) = delete;
712
713 protected:
714 CodeGenFunction& CGF;
715
716 public:
717 /// Enter a new cleanup scope.
718 explicit RunCleanupsScope(CodeGenFunction &CGF)
719 : PerformCleanup(true), CGF(CGF)
720 {
721 CleanupStackDepth = CGF.EHStack.stable_begin();
722 LifetimeExtendedCleanupStackSize =
723 CGF.LifetimeExtendedCleanupStack.size();
724 OldDidCallStackSave = CGF.DidCallStackSave;
725 CGF.DidCallStackSave = false;
726 OldCleanupScopeDepth = CGF.CurrentCleanupScopeDepth;
727 CGF.CurrentCleanupScopeDepth = CleanupStackDepth;
728 }
729
730 /// Exit this cleanup scope, emitting any accumulated cleanups.
731 ~RunCleanupsScope() {
732 if (PerformCleanup)
733 ForceCleanup();
734 }
735
736 /// Determine whether this scope requires any cleanups.
737 bool requiresCleanups() const {
738 return CGF.EHStack.stable_begin() != CleanupStackDepth;
739 }
740
741 /// Force the emission of cleanups now, instead of waiting
742 /// until this object is destroyed.
743 /// \param ValuesToReload - A list of values that need to be available at
744 /// the insertion point after cleanup emission. If cleanup emission created
745 /// a shared cleanup block, these value pointers will be rewritten.
746 /// Otherwise, they not will be modified.
747 void ForceCleanup(std::initializer_list<llvm::Value**> ValuesToReload = {}) {
748 assert(PerformCleanup && "Already forced cleanup");
749 CGF.DidCallStackSave = OldDidCallStackSave;
750 CGF.PopCleanupBlocks(CleanupStackDepth, LifetimeExtendedCleanupStackSize,
751 ValuesToReload);
752 PerformCleanup = false;
753 CGF.CurrentCleanupScopeDepth = OldCleanupScopeDepth;
754 }
755 };
756
757 // Cleanup stack depth of the RunCleanupsScope that was pushed most recently.
758 EHScopeStack::stable_iterator CurrentCleanupScopeDepth =
759 EHScopeStack::stable_end();

761 class LexicalScope : public RunCleanupsScope {
762 SourceRange Range;
763 SmallVector<const LabelDecl*, 4> Labels;
764 LexicalScope *ParentScope;
765
766 LexicalScope(const LexicalScope &) = delete;
767 void operator=(const LexicalScope &) = delete;
768
769 public:
770 /// Enter a new cleanup scope.
771 explicit LexicalScope(CodeGenFunction &CGF, SourceRange Range)
772 : RunCleanupsScope(CGF), Range(Range), ParentScope(CGF.CurLexicalScope) {
773 CGF.CurLexicalScope = this;
774 if (CGDebugInfo *DI = CGF.getDebugInfo())
775 DI->EmitLexicalBlockStart(CGF.Builder, Range.getBegin());
776 }
777
778 void addLabel(const LabelDecl *label) {
779 assert(PerformCleanup && "adding label to dead scope?");
780 Labels.push_back(label);
781 }
782
783 /// Exit this cleanup scope, emitting any accumulated
784 /// cleanups.
785 ~LexicalScope() {
786 if (CGDebugInfo *DI = CGF.getDebugInfo())
787 DI->EmitLexicalBlockEnd(CGF.Builder, Range.getEnd());
788
789 // If we should perform a cleanup, force them now. Note that
790 // this ends the cleanup scope before rescoping any labels.
791 if (PerformCleanup) {
792 ApplyDebugLocation DL(CGF, Range.getEnd());
793 ForceCleanup();
794 }
795 }
796
797 /// Force the emission of cleanups now, instead of waiting
798 /// until this object is destroyed.
799 void ForceCleanup() {
800 CGF.CurLexicalScope = ParentScope;
801 RunCleanupsScope::ForceCleanup();
802
803 if (!Labels.empty())
804 rescopeLabels();
805 }
806
807 bool hasLabels() const {
808 return !Labels.empty();
809 }
810
811 void rescopeLabels();
812 };

814 typedef llvm::DenseMap<const Decl *, Address> DeclMapTy;

816 /// The class used to assign some variables some temporarily addresses.
817 class OMPMapVars {
818 DeclMapTy SavedLocals;
819 DeclMapTy SavedTempAddresses;
820 OMPMapVars(const OMPMapVars &) = delete;
821 void operator=(const OMPMapVars &) = delete;
822
823 public:
824 explicit OMPMapVars() = default;
825 ~OMPMapVars() {
826 assert(SavedLocals.empty() && "Did not restored original addresses.");
827 };
828
829 /// Sets the address of the variable \p LocalVD to be \p TempAddr in
830 /// function \p CGF.
831 /// \return true if at least one variable was set already, false otherwise.
832 bool setVarAddr(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const VarDecl *LocalVD,
833 Address TempAddr) {
834 LocalVD = LocalVD->getCanonicalDecl();
835 // Only save it once.
836 if (SavedLocals.count(LocalVD)) return false;
837
838 // Copy the existing local entry to SavedLocals.
839 auto it = CGF.LocalDeclMap.find(LocalVD);
840 if (it != CGF.LocalDeclMap.end())
841 SavedLocals.try_emplace(LocalVD, it->second);
842 else
843 SavedLocals.try_emplace(LocalVD, Address::invalid());
844
845 // Generate the private entry.
846 QualType VarTy = LocalVD->getType();
847 if (VarTy->isReferenceType()) {
848 Address Temp = CGF.CreateMemTemp(VarTy);
849 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(TempAddr.getPointer(), Temp);
850 TempAddr = Temp;
851 }
852 SavedTempAddresses.try_emplace(LocalVD, TempAddr);
853
854 return true;
855 }
856
857 /// Applies new addresses to the list of the variables.
858 /// \return true if at least one variable is using new address, false
859 /// otherwise.
860 bool apply(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
861 copyInto(SavedTempAddresses, CGF.LocalDeclMap);
862 SavedTempAddresses.clear();
863 return !SavedLocals.empty();
864 }
865
866 /// Restores original addresses of the variables.
867 void restore(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
868 if (!SavedLocals.empty()) {
869 copyInto(SavedLocals, CGF.LocalDeclMap);
870 SavedLocals.clear();
871 }
872 }
873
874 private:
875 /// Copy all the entries in the source map over the corresponding
876 /// entries in the destination, which must exist.
877 static void copyInto(const DeclMapTy &Src, DeclMapTy &Dest) {
878 for (auto &Pair : Src) {
879 if (!Pair.second.isValid()) {
880 Dest.erase(Pair.first);
881 continue;
882 }
883
884 auto I = Dest.find(Pair.first);
885 if (I != Dest.end())
886 I->second = Pair.second;
887 else
888 Dest.insert(Pair);
889 }
890 }
891 };

1067 /// A non-RAII class containing all the information about a bound
1068 /// opaque value. OpaqueValueMapping, below, is a RAII wrapper for
1069 /// this which makes individual mappings very simple; using this
1070 /// class directly is useful when you have a variable number of
1071 /// opaque values or don't want the RAII functionality for some
1072 /// reason.
1073 class OpaqueValueMappingData {
1074 const OpaqueValueExpr *OpaqueValue;
1075 bool BoundLValue;
1076 CodeGenFunction::PeepholeProtection Protection;
1077
1078 OpaqueValueMappingData(const OpaqueValueExpr *ov,
1079 bool boundLValue)
1080 : OpaqueValue(ov), BoundLValue(boundLValue) {}
1081 public:
1082 OpaqueValueMappingData() : OpaqueValue(nullptr) {}
1083
1084 static bool shouldBindAsLValue(const Expr *expr) {
1085 // gl-values should be bound as l-values for obvious reasons.
1086 // Records should be bound as l-values because IR generation
1087 // always keeps them in memory. Expressions of function type
1088 // act exactly like l-values but are formally required to be
1089 // r-values in C.
1090 return expr->isGLValue() ||
1091 expr->getType()->isFunctionType() ||
1092 hasAggregateEvaluationKind(expr->getType());
1093 }
1094
1095 static OpaqueValueMappingData bind(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1096 const OpaqueValueExpr *ov,
1097 const Expr *e) {
1098 if (shouldBindAsLValue(ov))
1099 return bind(CGF, ov, CGF.EmitLValue(e));
1100 return bind(CGF, ov, CGF.EmitAnyExpr(e));
1101 }
1102
1103 static OpaqueValueMappingData bind(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1104 const OpaqueValueExpr *ov,
1105 const LValue &lv) {
1106 assert(shouldBindAsLValue(ov));
1107 CGF.OpaqueLValues.insert(std::make_pair(ov, lv));
1108 return OpaqueValueMappingData(ov, true);
1109 }
1110
1111 static OpaqueValueMappingData bind(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1112 const OpaqueValueExpr *ov,
1113 const RValue &rv) {
1114 assert(!shouldBindAsLValue(ov));
1115 CGF.OpaqueRValues.insert(std::make_pair(ov, rv));
1116
1117 OpaqueValueMappingData data(ov, false);
1118
1119 // Work around an extremely aggressive peephole optimization in
1120 // EmitScalarConversion which assumes that all other uses of a
1121 // value are extant.
1122 data.Protection = CGF.protectFromPeepholes(rv);
1123
1124 return data;
1125 }
1126
1127 bool isValid() const { return OpaqueValue != nullptr; }
1128 void clear() { OpaqueValue = nullptr; }
1129
1130 void unbind(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1131 assert(OpaqueValue && "no data to unbind!");
1132
1133 if (BoundLValue) {
1134 CGF.OpaqueLValues.erase(OpaqueValue);
1135 } else {
1136 CGF.OpaqueRValues.erase(OpaqueValue);
1137 CGF.unprotectFromPeepholes(Protection);
1138 }
1139 }
1140 };

1142 /// An RAII object to set (and then clear) a mapping for an OpaqueValueExpr.
1143 class OpaqueValueMapping {
1144 CodeGenFunction &CGF;
1145 OpaqueValueMappingData Data;
1146
1147 public:
1148 static bool shouldBindAsLValue(const Expr *expr) {
1149 return OpaqueValueMappingData::shouldBindAsLValue(expr);
1150 }
1151
1152 /// Build the opaque value mapping for the given conditional
1153 /// operator if it's the GNU ?: extension. This is a common
1154 /// enough pattern that the convenience operator is really
1155 /// helpful.
1156 ///
1157 OpaqueValueMapping(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1158 const AbstractConditionalOperator *op) : CGF(CGF) {

1174 "for OVE with no source expression");

1177 }
1178
1179 OpaqueValueMapping(CodeGenFunction &CGF,

1184
1185 OpaqueValueMapping(CodeGenFunction &CGF,

1188 : CGF(CGF), Data(OpaqueValueMappingData::bind(CGF, opaqueValue, rvalue)) {
1189 }
1190
1191 void pop() {
1192 Data.unbind(CGF);
1193 Data.clear();
1194 }
1195

1197 if (Data.isValid()) Data.unbind(CGF);
1198 }

1250 /// Handles cancellation exit points in OpenMP-related constructs.
1251 class OpenMPCancelExitStack {
1252 /// Tracks cancellation exit point and join point for cancel-related exit
1253 /// and normal exit.
1254 struct CancelExit {
1255 CancelExit() = default;
1256 CancelExit(OpenMPDirectiveKind Kind, JumpDest ExitBlock,
1257 JumpDest ContBlock)
1258 : Kind(Kind), ExitBlock(ExitBlock), ContBlock(ContBlock) {}
1259 OpenMPDirectiveKind Kind = OMPD_unknown;
1260 /// true if the exit block has been emitted already by the special
1261 /// emitExit() call, false if the default codegen is used.
1262 bool HasBeenEmitted = false;
1263 JumpDest ExitBlock;
1264 JumpDest ContBlock;
1265 };
1266
1267 SmallVector<CancelExit, 8> Stack;
1268
1269 public:
1270 OpenMPCancelExitStack() : Stack(1) {}
1271 ~OpenMPCancelExitStack() = default;
1272 /// Fetches the exit block for the current OpenMP construct.
1273 JumpDest getExitBlock() const { return Stack.back().ExitBlock; }
1274 /// Emits exit block with special codegen procedure specific for the related
1275 /// OpenMP construct + emits code for normal construct cleanup.
1276 void emitExit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, OpenMPDirectiveKind Kind,
1277 const llvm::function_ref<void(CodeGenFunction &)> CodeGen) {
1278 if (Stack.back().Kind == Kind && getExitBlock().isValid()) {
1279 assert(CGF.getOMPCancelDestination(Kind).isValid());
1280 assert(CGF.HaveInsertPoint());
1281 assert(!Stack.back().HasBeenEmitted);
1282 auto IP = CGF.Builder.saveAndClearIP();
1283 CGF.EmitBlock(Stack.back().ExitBlock.getBlock());
1284 CodeGen(CGF);
1285 CGF.EmitBranch(Stack.back().ContBlock.getBlock());
1286 CGF.Builder.restoreIP(IP);
1287 Stack.back().HasBeenEmitted = true;
1288 }
1289 CodeGen(CGF);
1290 }
1291 /// Enter the cancel supporting \a Kind construct.
1292 /// \param Kind OpenMP directive that supports cancel constructs.
1293 /// \param HasCancel true, if the construct has inner cancel directive,
1294 /// false otherwise.
1295 void enter(CodeGenFunction &CGF, OpenMPDirectiveKind Kind, bool HasCancel) {
1296 Stack.push_back({Kind,
1297 HasCancel ? CGF.getJumpDestInCurrentScope("cancel.exit")
1298 : JumpDest(),
1299 HasCancel ? CGF.getJumpDestInCurrentScope("cancel.cont")
1300 : JumpDest()});
1301 }
1302 /// Emits default exit point for the cancel construct (if the special one
1303 /// has not be used) + join point for cancel/normal exits.
1304 void exit(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1305 if (getExitBlock().isValid()) {
1306 assert(CGF.getOMPCancelDestination(Stack.back().Kind).isValid());
1307 bool HaveIP = CGF.HaveInsertPoint();
1308 if (!Stack.back().HasBeenEmitted) {
1309 if (HaveIP)
1310 CGF.EmitBranchThroughCleanup(Stack.back().ContBlock);
1311 CGF.EmitBlock(Stack.back().ExitBlock.getBlock());
1312 CGF.EmitBranchThroughCleanup(Stack.back().ContBlock);
1313 }
1314 CGF.EmitBlock(Stack.back().ContBlock.getBlock());
1315 if (!HaveIP) {
1316 CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
1317 CGF.Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
1318 }
1319 }
1320 Stack.pop_back();
1321 }
1322 };

1334 /// Increment the profiler's counter for the given statement by \p StepV.
1335 /// If \p StepV is null, the default increment is 1.
1336 void incrementProfileCounter(const Stmt *S, llvm::Value *StepV = nullptr) {
1337 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasProfileClangInstr())
1338 PGO.emitCounterIncrement(Builder, S, StepV);
1339 PGO.setCurrentStmt(S);
1340 }

1342 /// Get the profiler's count for the given statement.
1343 uint64_t getProfileCount(const Stmt *S) {
1344 Optional<uint64_t> Count = PGO.getStmtCount(S);
1345 if (!Count.hasValue())
1346 return 0;
1347 return *Count;
1348 }

1350 /// Set the profiler's current count.
1351 void setCurrentProfileCount(uint64_t Count) {
1352 PGO.setCurrentRegionCount(Count);
1353 }

1355 /// Get the profiler's current count. This is generally the count for the most
1356 /// recently incremented counter.

1358 return PGO.getCurrentRegionCount();

1702 /// Determines whether an EH cleanup is required to destroy a type
1703 /// with the given destruction kind.
1704 bool needsEHCleanup(QualType::DestructionKind kind) {
1705 switch (kind) {
1706 case QualType::DK_none:
1707 return false;
1708 case QualType::DK_cxx_destructor:
1709 case QualType::DK_objc_weak_lifetime:
1710 case QualType::DK_nontrivial_c_struct:
1711 return getLangOpts().Exceptions;
1712 case QualType::DK_objc_strong_lifetime:
1713 return getLangOpts().Exceptions &&
1714 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().ObjCAutoRefCountExceptions;
1715 }
1716 llvm_unreachable("bad destruction kind");
1717 }
1718
1719 CleanupKind getCleanupKind(QualType::DestructionKind kind) {
1720 return (needsEHCleanup(kind) ? NormalAndEHCleanup : NormalCleanup);
1721 }

2176 /// CreateTempAlloca - This creates an alloca and inserts it into the entry
2177 /// block if \p ArraySize is nullptr, otherwise inserts it at the current
2178 /// insertion point of the builder. The caller is responsible for setting an
2179 /// appropriate alignment on
2180 /// the alloca.
2181 ///
2182 /// \p ArraySize is the number of array elements to be allocated if it
2183 /// is not nullptr.
2184 ///
2185 /// LangAS::Default is the address space of pointers to local variables and
2186 /// temporaries, as exposed in the source language. In certain
2187 /// configurations, this is not the same as the alloca address space, and a
2188 /// cast is needed to lift the pointer from the alloca AS into
2189 /// LangAS::Default. This can happen when the target uses a restricted
2190 /// address space for the stack but the source language requires
2191 /// LangAS::Default to be a generic address space. The latter condition is
2192 /// common for most programming languages; OpenCL is an exception in that
2193 /// LangAS::Default is the private address space, which naturally maps
2194 /// to the stack.
2195 ///
2196 /// Because the address of a temporary is often exposed to the program in
2197 /// various ways, this function will perform the cast. The original alloca
2198 /// instruction is returned through \p Alloca if it is not nullptr.
2199 ///
2200 /// The cast is not performaed in CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast. This is
2201 /// more efficient if the caller knows that the address will not be exposed.
2202 llvm::AllocaInst *CreateTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty, const Twine &Name = "tmp",
2203 llvm::Value *ArraySize = nullptr);
2204 Address CreateTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty, CharUnits align,
2205 const Twine &Name = "tmp",
2206 llvm::Value *ArraySize = nullptr,
2207 Address *Alloca = nullptr);
2208 Address CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast(llvm::Type *Ty, CharUnits align,
2209 const Twine &Name = "tmp",
2210 llvm::Value *ArraySize = nullptr);
2211
2212 /// CreateDefaultAlignedTempAlloca - This creates an alloca with the
2213 /// default ABI alignment of the given LLVM type.
2214 ///
2215 /// IMPORTANT NOTE: This is *not* generally the right alignment for
2216 /// any given AST type that happens to have been lowered to the
2217 /// given IR type. This should only ever be used for function-local,
2218 /// IR-driven manipulations like saving and restoring a value. Do
2219 /// not hand this address off to arbitrary IRGen routines, and especially
2220 /// do not pass it as an argument to a function that might expect a
2221 /// properly ABI-aligned value.
2222 Address CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty,

2604 /// Situations in which we might emit a check for the suitability of a
2605 /// pointer or glvalue.
2606 enum TypeCheckKind {
2607 /// Checking the operand of a load. Must be suitably sized and aligned.
2608 TCK_Load,
2609 /// Checking the destination of a store. Must be suitably sized and aligned.
2610 TCK_Store,
2611 /// Checking the bound value in a reference binding. Must be suitably sized
2612 /// and aligned, but is not required to refer to an object (until the
2613 /// reference is used), per core issue 453.
2614 TCK_ReferenceBinding,
2615 /// Checking the object expression in a non-static data member access. Must
2616 /// be an object within its lifetime.
2617 TCK_MemberAccess,
2618 /// Checking the 'this' pointer for a call to a non-static member function.
2619 /// Must be an object within its lifetime.
2620 TCK_MemberCall,
2621 /// Checking the 'this' pointer for a constructor call.
2622 TCK_ConstructorCall,
2623 /// Checking the operand of a static_cast to a derived pointer type. Must be
2624 /// null or an object within its lifetime.
2625 TCK_DowncastPointer,
2626 /// Checking the operand of a static_cast to a derived reference type. Must
2627 /// be an object within its lifetime.
2628 TCK_DowncastReference,
2629 /// Checking the operand of a cast to a base object. Must be suitably sized
2630 /// and aligned.
2631 TCK_Upcast,
2632 /// Checking the operand of a cast to a virtual base object. Must be an
2633 /// object within its lifetime.
2634 TCK_UpcastToVirtualBase,
2635 /// Checking the value assigned to a _Nonnull pointer. Must not be null.
2636 TCK_NonnullAssign,
2637 /// Checking the operand of a dynamic_cast or a typeid expression. Must be
2638 /// null or an object within its lifetime.
2639 TCK_DynamicOperation
2640 };

2704 class AutoVarEmission {
2705 friend class CodeGenFunction;
2706
2707 const VarDecl *Variable;
2708
2709 /// The address of the alloca for languages with explicit address space
2710 /// (e.g. OpenCL) or alloca casted to generic pointer for address space
2711 /// agnostic languages (e.g. C++). Invalid if the variable was emitted
2712 /// as a global constant.
2713 Address Addr;
2714
2715 llvm::Value *NRVOFlag;
2716
2717 /// True if the variable is a __block variable that is captured by an
2718 /// escaping block.
2719 bool IsEscapingByRef;
2720
2721 /// True if the variable is of aggregate type and has a constant
2722 /// initializer.
2723 bool IsConstantAggregate;
2724
2725 /// Non-null if we should use lifetime annotations.
2726 llvm::Value *SizeForLifetimeMarkers;
2727
2728 /// Address with original alloca instruction. Invalid if the variable was
2729 /// emitted as a global constant.
2730 Address AllocaAddr;
2731
2732 struct Invalid {};
2733 AutoVarEmission(Invalid)
2734 : Variable(nullptr), Addr(Address::invalid()),
2735 AllocaAddr(Address::invalid()) {}
2736
2737 AutoVarEmission(const VarDecl &variable)
2738 : Variable(&variable), Addr(Address::invalid()), NRVOFlag(nullptr),
2739 IsEscapingByRef(false), IsConstantAggregate(false),
2740 SizeForLifetimeMarkers(nullptr), AllocaAddr(Address::invalid()) {}
2741
2742 bool wasEmittedAsGlobal() const { return !Addr.isValid(); }
2743
2744 public:
2745 static AutoVarEmission invalid() { return AutoVarEmission(Invalid()); }
2746
2747 bool useLifetimeMarkers() const {
2748 return SizeForLifetimeMarkers != nullptr;
2749 }
2750 llvm::Value *getSizeForLifetimeMarkers() const {
2751 assert(useLifetimeMarkers());
2752 return SizeForLifetimeMarkers;
2753 }
2754
2755 /// Returns the raw, allocated address, which is not necessarily
2756 /// the address of the object itself. It is casted to default
2757 /// address space for address space agnostic languages.
2758 Address getAllocatedAddress() const {
2759 return Addr;
2760 }
2761
2762 /// Returns the address for the original alloca instruction.
2763 Address getOriginalAllocatedAddress() const { return AllocaAddr; }
2764
2765 /// Returns the address of the object within this declaration.
2766 /// Note that this does not chase the forwarding pointer for
2767 /// __block decls.
2768 Address getObjectAddress(CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
2769 if (!IsEscapingByRef) return Addr;
2770
2771 return CGF.emitBlockByrefAddress(Addr, Variable, /*forward*/ false);
2772 }
2773 };

3542 class ConstantEmission {
3543 llvm::PointerIntPair<llvm::Constant*, 1, bool> ValueAndIsReference;
3544 ConstantEmission(llvm::Constant *C, bool isReference)
3545 : ValueAndIsReference(C, isReference) {}
3546 public:
3547 ConstantEmission() {}
3548 static ConstantEmission forReference(llvm::Constant *C) {
3549 return ConstantEmission(C, true);
3550 }
3551 static ConstantEmission forValue(llvm::Constant *C) {
3552 return ConstantEmission(C, false);
3553 }
3554
3555 explicit operator bool() const {
3556 return ValueAndIsReference.getOpaqueValue() != nullptr;
3557 }
3558
3559 bool isReference() const { return ValueAndIsReference.getInt(); }
3560 LValue getReferenceLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Expr *refExpr) const {
3561 assert(isReference());
3562 return CGF.MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(ValueAndIsReference.getPointer(),
3563 refExpr->getType());
3564 }
3565 // XXXAR: the CGF parameter exists to prevent inttoptr instructions
3566 // that are lowered incorrectly
3567 // See https://github.com/CTSRD-CHERI/llvm/issues/268
3568 llvm::Value *getValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
3569 assert(!isReference());
3570 llvm::Constant *C = ValueAndIsReference.getPointer();
3571 if (auto *PTy = dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(C->getType())) {
3572 if (auto *CE = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(C)) {
3573 if (CE->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::IntToPtr &&
3574 CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().isFatPointer(PTy)) {
3575 return CGF.setCapabilityIntegerValue(
3576 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(PTy), CE->getOperand(0));
3577 }
3578 }
3579 // TODO: are there any other exprs we need to special case?
3580 // assert(!CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().isFatPointer(PTy));
3581 }
3582 return C;
3583 }
3584 };

4267#ifndef NDEBUG
4268 // Determine whether the given argument is an Objective-C method
4269 // that may have type parameters in its signature.
4270 static bool isObjCMethodWithTypeParams(const ObjCMethodDecl *method) {
4271 const DeclContext *dc = method->getDeclContext();
4272 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *classDecl= dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(dc)) {
4273 return classDecl->getTypeParamListAsWritten();
4274 }
4275
4276 if (const ObjCCategoryDecl *catDecl = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(dc)) {
4277 return catDecl->getTypeParamList();
4278 }
4279
4280 return false;
4281 }

4283 template<typename T>
4284 static bool isObjCMethodWithTypeParams(const T *) { return false; }

4287 enum class EvaluationOrder {
4288 ///! No language constraints on evaluation order.
4289 Default,
4290 ///! Language semantics require left-to-right evaluation.
4291 ForceLeftToRight,
4292 ///! Language semantics require right-to-left evaluation.
4293 ForceRightToLeft

4296 /// EmitCallArgs - Emit call arguments for a function.
4297 template <typename T>
4298 void EmitCallArgs(CallArgList &Args, const T *CallArgTypeInfo,
4299 llvm::iterator_range<CallExpr::const_arg_iterator> ArgRange,
4300 AbstractCallee AC = AbstractCallee(),
4301 unsigned ParamsToSkip = 0,
4302 EvaluationOrder Order = EvaluationOrder::Default) {
4303 SmallVector<QualType, 16> ArgTypes;
4304 CallExpr::const_arg_iterator Arg = ArgRange.begin();
4305
4306 assert((ParamsToSkip == 0 || CallArgTypeInfo) &&
4307 "Can't skip parameters if type info is not provided");
4308 if (CallArgTypeInfo) {
4309#ifndef NDEBUG
4310 bool isGenericMethod = isObjCMethodWithTypeParams(CallArgTypeInfo);
4311#endif
4312
4313 // First, use the argument types that the type info knows about
4314 for (auto I = CallArgTypeInfo->param_type_begin() + ParamsToSkip,
4315 E = CallArgTypeInfo->param_type_end();
4316 I != E; ++I, ++Arg) {
4317 assert(Arg != ArgRange.end() && "Running over edge of argument list!");
4318 assert((isGenericMethod ||
4319 ((*I)->isVariablyModifiedType() ||
4320 (*I).getNonReferenceType()->isObjCRetainableType() ||
4321 getContext()
4322 .getCanonicalType((*I).getNonReferenceType())
4323 .getTypePtr() ==
4324 getContext()
4325 .getCanonicalType((*Arg)->getType())
4326 .getTypePtr())) &&
4327 "type mismatch in call argument!");
4328 ArgTypes.push_back(*I);
4329 }
4330 }
4331
4332 // Either we've emitted all the call args, or we have a call to variadic
4333 // function.
4334 assert((Arg == ArgRange.end() || !CallArgTypeInfo ||
4335 CallArgTypeInfo->isVariadic()) &&
4336 "Extra arguments in non-variadic function!");
4337
4338 // If we still have any arguments, emit them using the type of the argument.
4339 for (auto *A : llvm::make_range(Arg, ArgRange.end()))
4340 ArgTypes.push_back(CallArgTypeInfo ? getVarArgType(A) : A->getType());
4341
4342 EmitCallArgs(Args, ArgTypes, ArgRange, AC, ParamsToSkip, Order);
4343 }

4349 EvaluationOrder Order = EvaluationOrder::Default);

4468inline DominatingLLVMValue::saved_type
4469DominatingLLVMValue::save(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *value) {
4470 if (!needsSaving(value)) return saved_type(value, false);
4471
4472 // Otherwise, we need an alloca.
4473 auto align = CharUnits::fromQuantity(
4474 CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlignment(value->getType()));
4475 Address alloca =
4476 CGF.CreateTempAlloca(value->getType(), align, "cond-cleanup.save");
4477 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(value, alloca);
4478
4479 return saved_type(alloca.getPointer(), true);
4480}
4481
4482inline llvm::Value *DominatingLLVMValue::restore(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4483 saved_type value) {
4484 // If the value says it wasn't saved, trust that it's still dominating.
4485 if (!value.getInt()) return value.getPointer();
4486
4487 // Otherwise, it should be an alloca instruction, as set up in save().
4488 auto alloca = cast<llvm::AllocaInst>(value.getPointer());
4489 return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(alloca, alloca->getAlignment());
4490}
